The paper deals with wireless networks and their performance in terms of diversity and multiplexing. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also considers the cooperation of relay nodes and the time allocation between traffic directions, which are aspects of system design and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical models and analysis to derive results, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) categories.
